com.hcl.domino.richtext.annotation

Annotation Type StructureMember


  • @Retention(value=RUNTIME)
public @interface StructureMember

    • Required Element Summary

      Required Elements

    • Element Detail

      • name

        public abstract String name
        Returns:
        the name of the member in the structure

      • type

        public abstract Class<?> type
        Defines the Java type of the structure member. This may be one of:
        • A primitive number type
        • An enum that implements INumberEnum
        • A direct sub-interface of MemoryStructure

        If the value is unsigned in C, then unsigned() should be true and this type should be one primitive number size higher than the byte size of the storage type. For example, an unsigned WORD is represented by int.

        If the value is a bit field in C, such as a "Flags" field, then bitfield() should be true and this type should be the type of a single flag, and not a collection type.

        Returns:
        the Java type of the member

      • unsigned

        public abstract boolean unsigned
        Returns:
        whether the value of the structure member is an unsigned integer type
        Default:
        false

      • bitfield

        public abstract boolean bitfield
        Returns:
        whether the storage
        Default:
        false

      • length

        public abstract int length
        Specifies the length of the embedded structure array, when type() is an array type.
        Returns:
        the length of the structure array
        Default:
        1
